        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:02PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 102 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Boydton, or 10 miles southwest of South Hill. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Reduced visibility and minor flooding possible.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Mecklenburg County, including the following locations... Richardson,
Beechwood, Keats, John H Kerr Dam, Eppes Fork, Baskerville, Palmer
Springs, John H Kerr Reservoir, and Lake Gaston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
